\section{Competency Analysis and Analytics}
% ==============================================================

Beyond per-question adaptation, the system provides longitudinal competency tracking aligned with the APOT model's goal of holistic competency building~\cite{outay2024}.

\subsection{Competency Index with Recency Weighting}

The dashboard computes a Competency Index (CI) as a weighted average over the ten most recent completed tests:
\begin{equation}
\text{CI} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{\min(n,10)} \frac{1}{i} \cdot s_i}{\sum_{i=1}^{\min(n,10)} \frac{1}{i}}
\label{eq:ci}
\end{equation}
where $s_i$ is the score percentage of the $i$-th most recent test (ordered by recency). The harmonic weighting ensures recent performance has greater influence, reflecting the current competency state rather than historical averages.

\subsection{Domain-Level Performance Tracking}

The system tracks accuracy across three cognitive domains---Aptitude, Reasoning, and Verbal Ability---computing per-domain correct/total ratios. The weakest domain is identified and incorporated into personalized feedback, implementing the LSAA's function of domain-aware learner profiling.

\subsection{Competency Banding}

The leaderboard assigns competency labels based on score thresholds:
\begin{equation}
\text{Level} = 
\begin{cases}
\text{Expert}       & \text{if } s \geq 85 \\
\text{Advanced}     & \text{if } 70 \leq s < 85 \\
\text{Intermediate} & \text{if } 50 \leq s < 70 \\
\text{Beginner}     & \text{if } s < 50
\end{cases}
\label{eq:bands}
\end{equation}

These bands, combined with per-domain accuracy and difficulty progression data stored in \texttt{AdaptiveLearningHistory}, provide a multi-dimensional view of student competency that goes beyond a single score.

% ==============================================================
\section{Data Models}
% ==============================================================

The persistence layer comprises three interconnected models that provide a complete audit trail for every assessment session.

\textbf{StudentTestResult} stores session-level metadata: user, topic, initial and final difficulty, score percentage (auto-computed as $\frac{\text{correct}}{\text{total}} \times 100$), status, timestamps, and JSON fields for answers data, adaptive analysis, and difficulty progression.

\textbf{QuestionPerformance} stores per-question details: the question text, options, selected and correct answers, correctness flag, time taken, AI-predicted difficulty (\texttt{predicted\_difficulty}), recommended next difficulty (\texttt{next\_difficulty}), and the full CrewAI reasoning and recommendation text. A unique constraint on \texttt{(test\_result, question\_number)} ensures data integrity.

\textbf{AdaptiveLearningHistory} provides a focused record of the APOT pipeline output per question: current difficulty, next difficulty, correctness, time taken, and the SOLTA agent's reasoning and recommendation.

