The rule set covers all six combinations in the $\{\text{Correct}, \text{Incorrect}\} \times \{\text{Easy}, \text{Medium}, \text{Hard}\}$ space, ensuring no undefined transitions exist. The design prevents two failure modes common in adaptive systems: (1)~\textit{oscillation}, where a student alternates between difficulty levels without convergence, is mitigated by the ``maintain mastery'' Hard+Correct rule; and (2)~\textit{indefinite floor trapping}, where a student is stuck at the lowest level, is mitigated by the Easy+Correct escalation to Medium.

